SIMPLE: notching
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Notching
<hw>Notch"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of making
notches; the act of cutting into small hollows.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The small hollow, or hollows, cut; a notch or
notches.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Carp.)</fld> <def>A method of joining timbers,
scantling, etc., by notching them, as at the ends, and overlapping or
interlocking the notched portions.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Engin.)</fld> <def>A method of excavating, as in a
bank, by a series of cuttings side by side. See also
<er>Gulleting</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Notchweed</ent>⟦br⟧
